snippet.textDisplay:
Jaclyn . Do me a favour and take a deep breathe right now - seriously . It helps . And I can feel your tension girl .
But on a serious note you don’t owe anybody an explanation for your weight . That’s crazy . You have been going through so much and you self medicated .. you’re human . I personally am an addict in recovery and I used to be 120 pounds . I gained 100 POUNDS when I got pregnant . The weight is still on for the most part but I lost a bit . I’m learning to love the new me while still eating healthy and taking care of myself . I don’t think most people think you are here to “only sell us stuff” . YOU ARE FOLLOWING YOUR DREAMS . I only WISH I could have my own makeup line . That is the coolest thing ever . Never stop believing in yourself . You are capable of SO MUCH . Everybody makes mistakes “everybody has those days”
Channeling my inner Hannah Montana 😜
But no seriously you can’t please everybody 24/7 . Nobody is EVER going to be 100 percent satisfied with what you do . People are critics and you’re in the lime light . But there are people who love what you do so keep doing it for them and for yourself .
Either way I hope you see this . I love you girl . I went through therapy because I have panic disorder and my anxiety attacks were hospitalizing me for a while in 2018 after I lost my spouse . I didn’t want to do the medication route because I knew myself and I knew I wanted to fight this the hard way so I did LOTS of therapy and it WORKS . It seriously helped me . It takes time but you will get there ❤️
